from jek subject watt misquote heath terrance heath write i realize i enter thi discussion rather late but i do have one question wa it a reagan appointee jame watt a pentacostal christian i think who wa the secretary of the interior who saw no problem with deforestation since we be live in the last day and our would be the last generation to see the redwood anyway for the record on february at a house of representative interior committee meeting rep jame weaver d ore ask watt whether you agree that we should save some of my scenic resource for my child not just gobble them up all at once watt answer wa absolutely that be the delicate balance the secretary of the interior must have to be steward for the natural resource for thi generation a well a future generation i do not know how many future generation we can count on before the lord return whatever it be we have to manage with a skill to have the resource need for future generation my source be a column by rowland evan and robert novak on the op-ed page of the washington post for friday august your jame kiefer 